today.

00:00:51.410 --> 00:00:54.880
The people who would become the Jews, were
just one of many tribal peoples eking out

00:00:54.880 --> 00:01:00.540
an existence in that not-very fertile crescent
world of Mesopotamia after the agricultural revolution.

00:01:00.540 --> 00:01:04.920
The Hebrews initially worshiped many gods,
making sacrifices to them in order to bring

00:01:04.920 --> 00:01:09.100
good weather and good fortune. But they eventually
developed a religion centered around an idea

00:01:09.100 --> 00:01:12.159
that would become key to the other great western
religions.

00:01:12.159 --> 00:01:17.060
This was monotheism, the idea that there is
only one true god (or at least that if there

00:01:17.060 --> 00:01:21.329
are other gods around, they are total lameoids).
The Hebrews developed a second concept that

00:01:21.329 --> 00:01:26.209
is key to their religion as well: the idea
of the covenant, a deal with God.

00:01:26.209 --> 00:01:30.999
The main man in this, the big macher was Abraham.
Not to make this too much of a scripture lesson,

00:01:30.999 --> 00:01:34.670
but it’s kind of hard to understand the
Jews without understanding Abraham, or Abram

00:01:34.670 --> 00:01:40.099
as he was known before he had his big conversation
with God. Recorded in Genesis 17: "When Abram

00:01:40.099 --> 00:01:46.009
was ninety years and nine, the LORD appeared
to Abram, and said unto him, 'I am the Almighty

00:01:46.009 --> 00:01:49.689
God; walk before me, and be thou perfect.'
" And I’m a make a covenant with you and

00:01:49.689 --> 00:01:52.740
a bunch of cool things will happen like you’re
