Thanks for keeping it clean, Thought Bubble.

00:02:33.110 --> 00:02:35.100
So, some important things about this god:

00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:39.190
One, singularity. He — and I’m using the
masculine pronoun because that’s what Hebrew

00:02:39.190 --> 00:02:42.780
prayers use — does not want you to put any
gods before Him.

00:02:42.780 --> 00:02:47.450
He is also transcendent, having always existed
and he is deeply personal – he chats with

00:02:47.450 --> 00:02:52.480
prophets, sends locusts, etc. But he doesn’t
take corporeal form like the Greek and Roman Gods do.

00:02:52.480 --> 00:02:57.880
He is also involved in history, like he will
destroy cities, and bring floods, and determine

00:02:57.880 --> 00:03:02.870
the outcome of wars, and possibly football
games. Stan, no! FOOTBALL games!

00:03:02.870 --> 00:03:06.600
Probably most important to us today, and certainly
most important to Jesus, this god demands

00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:11.380
moral righteousness and social justice. So,
this is the god of the Hebrews, Yahweh, and

00:03:11.380 --> 00:03:15.490
despite many ups and downs, the Jewish people
have stuck with him for- according to the

00:03:15.490 --> 00:03:18.710
Hebrew calendar, at least- over 5700 years.

00:03:18.710 --> 00:03:23.000
And He has stuck by them too, despite the
Jews being, on occasion, something of a disappointment

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:27.319
to him. Which leads to various miseries, and
also to a tradition of prophets who speak

00:03:27.319 --> 00:03:32.250
for God and warn the people to get back on
the right path lest there be more miseries.

00:03:32.250 --> 00:03:35.800
Which brings us back to our friends, the Romans.
By the time that Jesus was born, the land

00:03:35.800 --> 00:03:40.130
of the Israelites had been absorbed into the
Roman Empire as the province of Judea. At

00:03:40.130 --> 00:03:43.970
the time of Jesus’s birth, Judea was under
the control of Herod the Great, best known

00:03:43.970 --> 00:03:48.280
for building the massive temple in Jerusalem,
that the Romans would later destroy.

00:03:48.280 --> 00:03:53.000
And by the time Jesus died, an expanded Judea
was under the rule of Herod Antipater. Also,

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:57.120
unhelpfully, known as Herod. Both Herods ultimately
took their orders from the Romans, and they

00:03:57.120 --> 00:04:01.540
both show up on the list of rulers who are
oppressive to the Jews, partly because there’s

00:04:01.540 --> 00:04:04.319
never that much religious freedom in an empire.

00:04:04.319 --> 00:04:10.399
Unless you are, wait for it... The Mongols
[Mongoltage]

00:04:10.400 --> 00:04:14.460
or the Persians. Also, they were Hellenizers,
bringing in Greek theater and architecture,

00:04:14.470 --> 00:04:18.620
and rationalism. And in response to those
Hellenistic influences, there were a lot of

00:04:18.620 --> 00:04:23.340
preachers trying to get the Jews to return
to the traditions and the godly ways of the

00:04:23.340 --> 00:04:27.469
past, including the Sadducees, and the Pharisees,
and the Essenes, and the Zealots.

00:04:27.469 --> 00:04:31.120
And one of those preachers, who didn’t fit
comfortably into any of these four groups,

00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:35.389
was Jesus of Nazareth. Jesus was a preacher
who spread his message of peace, love and,

00:04:35.389 --> 00:04:40.829
above all, justice, across Judea over the
course of his actually average-length life for his time.

00:04:40.829 --> 00:04:46.020
He was remarkably charismatic, attracting
a small but incredibly loyal group of followers,

00:04:46.020 --> 00:04:49.740
and he was said to perform miracles — although
it’s worth noting that miracles weren’t

00:04:49.740 --> 00:04:51.539
terribly uncommon at the time.

00:04:51.539 --> 00:04:56.199
Jesus’s message was particularly resonant
to the poor and downtrodden and pretty radical

00:04:56.199 --> 00:05:00.430
in its anti-authoritarian stance. He said
it was easier for a camel to get through the

00:05:00.430 --> 00:05:04.330
eye of a needle than for a rich man to get
to heaven, he said the meek were blessed,

00:05:04.330 --> 00:05:08.029
that the last would be first and the first
would be last — all of which was kind of

00:05:08.029 --> 00:05:13.169
threatening to the powers that be, who accordingly
had him arrested, tried and then executed

00:05:13.169 --> 00:05:16.309
in the normal method of killing rebels at
that time: crucifixion.

00:05:16.309 --> 00:05:20.860
Also, just to put this question to bed, the
Romans crucified Jesus, because he was a

00:05:20.860 --> 00:05:28.120
threat to their authority. Later traditions saying that the
Jews killed Jesus? Very unfortunate, also, very untrue.

00:05:28.120 --> 00:05:30.520
We’re not going to discuss Jesus’s divinity,
because:

00:05:30.539 --> 00:05:35.460
1. This isn’t a theology class, and
2. Flame wars on the Internet make me so uncomfortable that

00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:38.629
I have to turn to camera 2. Hi there camera
2, I’m here to remind you that

00:05:38.629 --> 00:05:42.599
3. Fighting over such things, like fighting
over whether the proverbial cake is a lie,

00:05:42.599 --> 00:05:46.749
rarely accomplishes anything, plus
4. What matters to us is the historical fact

00:05:46.749 --> 00:05:52.449
that people at the time believed that Jesus
was the Messiah, the Anointed One, the son

00:05:52.449 --> 00:05:56.210
of God. And they believed that he would return
some day to redeem the world.

00:05:56.210 --> 00:05:58.379
Which leads us to two questions about Christianity:

00:05:58.379 --> 00:06:02.909
First, Why did this small group of people
believe this? And second, why and how did

00:06:02.909 --> 00:06:05.370
that belief become so widespread?

00:06:05.370 --> 00:06:07.309
So why would people believe that Jesus was
the Messiah?

00:06:07.309 --> 00:06:11.339
First. The Jews had a long tradition of believing
that a savior who would come to them in a

00:06:11.339 --> 00:06:15.939
time of trouble. And Judea under the rule
of Herod and the Romans... definitely a time of trouble.

00:06:15.940 --> 00:06:19.680
And many of the prophecies about this savior
point to someone whose life looks a lot like

00:06:19.689 --> 00:06:24.699
Jesus's. For instance, Isaiah 53 says the
person will be misunderstood and mistreated,

00:06:24.699 --> 00:06:29.639
just like Jesus was: “He was despised, and
rejected by men; a man of sorrows, and acquainted

00:06:29.640 --> 00:06:35.580
with grief: and as one from whom men hide
their face he was despised; and we didn't respect him.”

00:06:35.580 --> 00:06:39.520
And a lot of the prophecies like Daniel 7:14,
for instance, explained that when the Messiah

00:06:39.520 --> 00:06:44.259
comes there will be this awesome, new, everlasting
kingdom. And that had to sound pretty good

00:06:44.259 --> 00:06:46.589
to people who’d had their autonomy taken
away from them.

00:06:46.589 --> 00:06:50.039
So some religious Jews saw Jesus in those
prophecies and came to believe either during

00:06:50.039 --> 00:06:54.289
his life or shortly thereafter, that he was
the messiah. Most of them thought the new

00:06:54.289 --> 00:06:58.599
everlasting kingdom was right around the corner,
which is probably why no one bothered to write

00:06:58.599 --> 00:07:03.259
down much about the life of Jesus for several
decades, by which time it was clear that we

00:07:03.259 --> 00:07:06.659
might have to wait a bit for this brilliant
new everlasting kingdom.

00:07:06.659 --> 00:07:10.180
I should note, by the way, that the idea of
a messiah was not unique to the Jews at the

00:07:10.180 --> 00:07:13.930
time. Even the Romans got in on the action,
for instance, the Roman poet Virgil wrote

00:07:13.930 --> 00:07:18.289
of a boy who: “Shall free the earth from
never-ceasing fear, he shall receive the life

00:07:18.289 --> 00:07:22.699
of gods, and see Heroes with gods commingling.”
Sound familiar?

00:07:22.699 --> 00:07:26.889
But Virgil was writing about Emperor Augustus
in that poem, not Jesus, which points again

00:07:26.889 --> 00:07:31.409
to the similarities between the two. Both
called sons of God. Both sent to free the

00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:35.809
earth from never-ceasing fear. But one ruled
the largest empire in the world; and the other

00:07:35.809 --> 00:07:39.979
believed that empire, and the world, needed
to change dramatically.

00:07:39.979 --> 00:07:45.009
So why did the less wealthy and famous son
of God become by far the more influential?

00:07:45.009 --> 00:07:47.629
Well, here are three possible historical reasons:

00:07:47.629 --> 00:07:52.309
Reason #1: The Romans continued to make things
bad for the Jews. In fact, things got much

00:07:52.309 --> 00:07:59.329
worse for the Jews, especially after they launched
a revolt between 66-73 CE, which did not go well.

00:07:59.329 --> 00:08:03.220
By the time the dust settled, the Romans had
destroyed the Temple and expelled the Jews

00:08:03.229 --> 00:08:06.829
from Judea, beginning what we now know
as the Jewish Diaspora.

00:08:06.829 --> 00:08:10.680
And without a Temple or geographic unity,
the Jews had to solidify what it meant to

00:08:10.680 --> 00:08:14.809
be a Jew and what the basic tenants of the
religion were. This forced the followers of

00:08:14.809 --> 00:08:18.749
Jesus to make a decision: were they going
to continue to be Jews following stricter

00:08:18.749 --> 00:08:22.460
laws set forth by rabbis, or were they going
to be something else.

00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:25.659
The decision to open up their religion to
non-Jews, people who weren’t part of the

00:08:25.659 --> 00:08:30.199
covenant, is the central reason that Christianity
could become a world religion instead of just

00:08:30.199 --> 00:08:33.940
a sect of Judaism. And it probably didn’t
hurt that the main proponent of sticking with

00:08:33.940 --> 00:08:37.880
Judaism was James, Jesus’s brother, who
was killed by the Romans.

00:08:37.880 --> 00:08:42.830
Reason #2: Is related to Reason #1 and it’s
all about a dude named Saul. No, not that

00:08:42.830 --> 00:08:45.820
Saul. Yes, Saul of Tarsus, thank you.

00:08:45.820 --> 00:08:50.090
Saul, having received a vision on the road
to Damascus, became Paul and began visiting

00:08:50.090 --> 00:08:55.040
and sending letters to Jesus followers throughout
the Mediterranean. And it was Paul who emphatically

00:08:55.040 --> 00:08:59.320
declared that Jesus followers did NOT have
to be Jews, that they did not have to be circumcised

00:08:59.320 --> 00:09:01.770
or keep to Jewish laws or any of that stuff.

00:09:01.770 --> 00:09:05.030
This opened the floodgates for thousands of
people to convert to this new religion. And

00:09:05.030 --> 00:09:08.320
the other thing to remember about Paul is
that he was a Roman citizen, which meant that

00:09:08.320 --> 00:09:12.030
he could travel freely throughout the Roman
Empire. This allowed him to make his case

00:09:12.030 --> 00:09:15.790
to lots of different people and facilitated
the geographic spread of Christianity.

