And lastly, Christianity was born and flourished
an empire with a common language that allowed

00:10:17.710 --> 00:10:21.520
for its spread. And crucially, it was also
an Empire in decline.

00:10:21.520 --> 00:10:25.720
Like even by the end of the first century
CE, Rome was on its way down. And for the

00:10:25.720 --> 00:10:29.120
average person, and even for some elites,
things weren’t as good as they had been,

00:10:29.120 --> 00:10:33.300
if fact they were getting worse so fast that you
might have thought the end of the world was coming.

00:10:33.300 --> 00:10:36.940
And Roman religion offered no promise of an
afterlife, and a bunch of squabbling whiny

00:10:36.950 --> 00:10:42.660
gods - sorry if I offended adherents to Roman
religion, but seriously, they squabble. So

00:10:42.660 --> 00:10:46.600
even though early Christians were persecuted
by the Roman Empire and sometimes fed to the

00:10:46.600 --> 00:10:50.790
lions and other animals, the religion continued
to grow, albeit slowly.

00:10:50.790 --> 00:10:54.870
But then as the Roman decline continued, Emperor
Constantine allowed the worship of Jesus and

00:10:54.870 --> 00:10:58.420
then eventually converted to Christianity
himself. And then the religion really took

00:10:58.420 --> 00:11:01.640
off. I mean, Rome wasn’t what it used to
be, but everybody still wanted to be like

00:11:01.640 --> 00:11:05.170
the Emperor. And soon enough there was a new
son of God on coins.

